<%= render 'shared/navbar' %>

  <!-- Landing Page Header -->
  <header class="text-center py-20 bg-blue-200">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800">Welcome to the IMDb Movies Project</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-xl text-gray-600">Explore the world of movies, actors, and directors!</p>
  </header>

  <!-- Project Description -->
  <section class="container mx-auto p-6 bg-white mt-12 rounded shadow-lg">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">Project Overview</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-700">
      This project is a simple IMDb-like application that allows you to manage movies, actors, and directors.
      The database includes tables for actors, directors, movies, and reviews, each of which is linked to create relationships
      between them. Here's a brief overview of the key tables in the database:
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Table Descriptions -->
  <section class="container mx-auto p-6 bg-white mt-6 rounded shadow-lg">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">Database Tables</h2>

    <h3 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700">1. Actors Table</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      The <strong>actors</strong> table stores information about actors, including their name, birth year, nationality,
      and their geographical coordinates (latitude and longitude).
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700">2. Directors Table</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      The <strong>directors</strong> table contains details about movie directors, such as their name, birth year, and nationality.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700">3. Movies Table</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      The <strong>movies</strong> table stores information about each movie, including its title, genre, rating, budget,
      revenue, and an overview of the movie. It also includes the movie's release date.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700">4. Reviews Table</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      The <strong>reviews</strong> table stores user reviews for movies. Each review is linked to a specific movie and includes
      the review text and the rating given.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700">5. Movie Actors Table</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      The <strong>movie_actors</strong> table represents a many-to-many relationship between movies and actors. Each entry in this
      table links a specific actor to a movie.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700">6. Movie Directors Table</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      The <strong>movie_directors</strong> table represents a many-to-many relationship between movies and directors. It links
      directors to the movies they have directed.
    </p>
  </section>

